##In memory of Liu Zhimingjun

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

By Wei Jiaming, Wen Xiaoxiao, Xue Shasha, Wang Xuanhui, Huang Jijie, Tang Qi, thepaper.cn

Intern, Meng jin-jin, Jung Wook

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Liu Zhiming leads the team to participate in the first Wuhan Marathon medical security work. (sixth from left is Liu Zhiming.)

Liu Zhiming left for good.

His wife, Cai Liping, remembers a message he sent her from the Intensive Care Unit of Wuchang Hospital on the night of February 3.

It was the 10th day after Liu Zhiming was sent to the intensive-care unit, a muscular, middle aged man in his fifties who was 1.8 meters tall and too weak to speak.

"I had a rough night last night. I thought I was going to die because of lack of oxygen, restlessness and sweating all over. I had a suction machine this morning and I felt much better. "

She was busy in the intensive care unit of the Guanggu Ward of Wuhan's Third Hospital, where she was the head nurse.

The next day at noon, Cai Liping finished seven consecutive hours of work, hurriedly took out a cell phone, check whether her husband returned the message. Before entering the ward, she dialed four video calls in succession, all did not connect.

"I'll keep you company. " The video finally connected.

At the other end of the screen, Liu shook his head.

Liu Ruen, director of neurosurgery at Peking University People's Hospital, and Liu Zhiming have been close friends for 20 years.

February 17 at 9:30 pm, learned that Liu Zhiming Dying News, Liu Ruen rushed to call him, but always no one answered.

Since the outbreak of the epidemic, two people have been through a telephone on the second day of the Lunar New Year, the phone, Liu Zhiming Voice Hoarse, to friends to tell the hospital bed shortage, feel difficult.

Did Not say a few words, together in the line of busy Liu ruen hastily hung up the phone. He did not know that Liu Zhiming had been admitted to the intensive care unit with a low-grade fever for a week before falling ill.

On Feb. 18, after 17 hours of ECMO treatment, Liu left.

A "good-bye" on the phone is goodbye forever.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
After the right second Liu Zhiming, before the middle is Wang Lunchang, before the left one Tu Han Jun, after the left Second Roger

At the last moment

Back at 4 pm on January 21, Wuchang Hospital was requisitioned as the first designated hospital in Wuhan to receive patients with fever due to the outbreak.

The deputy director of Wuchang Hospital, Huang Guofu, said that after receiving the instructions, they were given only two hours to carry out the renovation of fever clinics. A mobilization meeting of the functional departments was held at 4:30, and at 5:00 all clinical first-level directors were to be convened for discussion, one meeting after another, Liu Zhiming was involved.

Wuchang's disciplinary chief, Hong Yi, told The Paper www.thepaper.cn  that there were still 499 patients in the hospital and the transfer needed to be completed within three days, as the hospital needed temporary renovation. Hospital officials, including Liu Zhiming, were on call 24 hours a day and held overnight meetings, to discuss staffing arrangements.

His wife, Cai Liping, 47, is the head nurse of the Intensive Care Unit of the Guanggu district of Wuhan Third Hospital. She was a little uneasy at the time, as early as January 20 or so, her husband began a slight fever, general malaise. At the time, however, she did not realize that the reaction in her husband was a symptom of neocoronary pneumonia.

Hong Yi revealed that in the early stages of "preparing for war" , Liu Zhiming had entered the ICU wearing a first-class protective device because he did not have a comprehensive awareness of the prevention and control of the epidemic. At that time, there were many suspected patients lying in the ICU who were infected with or had started at that time, "He's an expert on the outside world, " he said. "He needs to get to the bottom of every patient. ".

On January 22, around 6 or 7 a.m. , Cai Liping received another call from Liu Zhiming, saying that the hospital was very busy and he would not go home. He was going to work immediately. "I felt that he was breathing a little too fast, so I told him that he was breathing a little problem and could not be underestimated, " Cai Liping said

Also on this day, Liu Zhiming also had a meal with Hongyi in the unit canteen, had said his eyes a little uncomfortable. "You can eat, drink and run, " he joked, thinking he was joking. "You don't look sick anywhere. "

On the same day, Liu Zhiming had his temperature measured twice, once at thirty-six degrees and once at thirty-seven degrees. In the afternoon, he called his wife to tell her that he was walking with asthma and suspected infection, and had been treated at Wuchang Hospital. The next day, Liu Zhiming was diagnosed. A total of 495 new cases were confirmed in Wuhan on January 23, according to the Provincial Health Commission.

On January 24, the eve of what was supposed to be a reunion, Liu Zhiming became seriously ill and was transferred to the intensive-care unit of Wuchang Hospital. At this time of Cai Liping has also returned to his post in advance, only through video phone to understand the condition of his husband.

After hospitalization, Liu Zhiming at first high fever does not retreat, accompany asthma; after high fever recedes, appear again hotheaded; once oxygen saturation is low to 80, how all can not go up. Even so, that his condition deteriorated, Liu Zhiming still told the attending doctor, "If in case, do not intubation rescue. ".

On the afternoon of Feb. 4, after a seven-hour shift, Ms. Tsai, dressed in a dark green, short-sleeved hand-wash, leaned over a pile of cardboard boxes to inventory medical equipment.

Before entering the ward in the morning, she called her husband, Liu Zhiming, who was lying in the intensive care unit of Wuchang Hospital, four times.

The night before, Liu Zhiming sent Cai Liping a wechat message saying, "I was up all night trying to get oxygen. I thought I was going to die. I was out of oxygen, restless and sweating all over. I had a vacuum pump this morning, and it was much better! "

After the video call was connected, Cai Liping said to Liu Zhiming, "let me accompany you. " At the other end of the screen, unable to speak, Liu Zhiming shook his head.

According to the Changjiang daily, on January 27, the Guanggu Hospital District of Wuhan No. 3 Hospital began to receive patients. Only one and a half days later, all the wards were fully occupied. Cai Liping's intensive care unit was under great pressure.

One is lying in the ICU husband, the other is also suffering from new crown pneumonia patients, a few times, she was hard-hearted, want to put down the hands of the work to accompany, but were rejected by Liu Zhiming.

On February 14, Liu Zhiming was transferred from Wuchang Hospital to Tongji Hospital in the sino-french new city hospital area and began receiving intubation treatment.

On the morning of Feb. 17, the hospital gave him ECMO First Aid, and a day later, he died of exhaustion.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Wang Lunchang, the 80-year-old honorary director of the Taihe Hospital in Shiyan City and former party secretary, also lamented, and sent Liu Zhiming off with a poem

The sunshine boy with the needlepoint

After learning of Liu Zhiming's death, Liu Jiamin, secretary, director and researcher of the Shiyan Emergency Center, grabbed the phone and called the people he had crossed paths with one by one.

A cherubic face, with a smile and toothy smile, it was sunny -- as if Liu Zhiming had lived forever at the age of 22.

In July 1991,22-year-old Liu Zhiming graduated from the Wuhan University School of Medicine Department and was assigned to clinical work in neurosurgery in the third ward outside the former Yunyang district people's hospital.

At that time, Liu Jiamin is the hospital's propaganda section chief and the Youth League secretary, or the Communist Youth League member Liu Zhiming is the section office of the group, often participate in youth activities, straightforward, warm and generous.

"surgeons are energetic, they work hard, they study hard, and they like him, " Liu told The Paper. When he started out, he studied under Tu Hanjun, then dean of the hospital and now party secretary of Hubei Medical College.

Write the medical records, rounds, do surgery, Liu Zhiming every detail. Brain surgery is a delicate work, the industry known as "needlepoint surgery" , need to be bold and careful, "he can do it. ".

In the early 1990s, although Yunyang Hospital is the fourth largest hospital in Hubei Province, but the hospital undergraduate students are not many, Fresh Off the Boat Liu Zhiming nature was "pushed" on the operating table.

In 1993, fresh out of the scalpel, Liu Zhiming took on a delicate case: a three year old girl who had fallen from a building, suffered severe brain trauma, and was in a coma for more than 60 days.

At that time, the girl's father almost wanted to give up, Liu Zhiming is a bed doctor, responsible for the care, he encouraged the child's mother, had a similar case successfully rescued precedent, to ease her anxiety.

Liu Jiamin remembers, Liu Zhiming still can accompany the mother of the child to sing together, give the child in comatose massage. Eventually, a miracle happened.

After work, Liu Zhiming likes to follow the teacher to ponder the technology, he once said to Liu Jiamin, for the future, I do not have too many ideas, is to be a good doctor, to do surgery well.

Like many rural children, Liu Zhiming, whose family lives in rural Shiyan, is simple-minded and hard-working. When he saw that his colleague lived on a high floor, he offered to help carry the LPG tanks.

In his spare time on weekends, Liu and his young colleagues gather at the single workers'dormitory in Qingsongpo, where they sing, dance and play basketball. Liu Jiamin, secretary of the Youth League Committee, Organized Hospital colleagues to create their own "cultural festival" . One of the links was a fashion show. Liu Zhiming, who was 1.8 meters tall, walked in wearing a suit and "amazed" the whole scene.

"Back then everyone was young, the canteen was cheap, the salary was average, but everyone was optimistic and there was no gap between them. " In the years without mobile phones and computers, listening to live was a big pastime for doctors. Liu Zhiming always came early to help the band set up the venue and move the instruments.

In 1995, Liu Zhiming left Shiyan to work in Wuhan. Before leaving, Liu Jiamin also told him that the opportunity was good. "It's good to work in Wuhan, I'll see you later. " However, because of their busy work, they met mostly at meetings, but Liu Zhiming still politely asked: "How are you doing? "

After the outbreak, Liu Jiamin in the same line did not know, Liu Zhiming has been infected. Until the night of February 17, he learned from a friend Liu Zhiming has been on the artificial lung, the heart had the worst plan.

Doctors can't heal themselves.

This time, Liu Zhiming, who had saved many lives, could not save himself.

"Work Your ass off. "

Whether in the Yunyang Hospital, the Wuhan Sanyuan or the Wuchang Hospital, Liu Zhiming's fighting strength is almost unknown.

Li Wei, a 39-year-old neurosurgeon at the Wuhan Institute of Neurosurgery who was one of the doctors led by Liu Zhiming's predecessor, sees the institute's Progress as founded and driven by Liu Zhiming.

He told The Paper that the Department of neurosurgery was not an independent department in Wuhan's Trigeminal Neuralgia, and that during his tenure, Liu had actively contacted experts at the People's Hospital of Peking University to conduct surgical research on trigeminal NEURALGIA and hemifacial spasm.
The expert in Li Wei's mouth is precisely Liu Zhiming's good friend Liu Ruen. While studying for her phd in neurosurgery at the Wuhan Union Hospital, she got to know Liu Zhiming, who was also studying at Union Medical College.

Liu Ruen remember, had been working for many years Liu Zhiming still insist on weekends reading, learning business, two people so close. He found that Liu Zhiming extremely dedicated, whether on duty or not, he would get up in the middle of the night with the teacher on stage for surgery.

After graduation, she was assigned to work in Beijing, specializing in functional neurosurgery, where microvascular decompression is used to treat facial spasm and trigeminal NEURALGIA. After Liu Zhiming assumes office, also wants to do this therapy in Wuhan.
In order to bring in experts from Beijing, Liu Zhiming drove to Wuhan several times himself to pick up Liu Ruen, who had been dispatched by the Organization Department of the Communist Party of China Central Committee and was serving as the vice president of the Jiangxi Provincial People's Hospital.

On a Friday, Liu told the paper, a meeting in his courtyard stayed open until after 6 p.m. , and Liu drove to Nanchang at noon, waiting until he left the meeting before picking him up in Wuhan. When he arrived, it was midnight.

On another Sunday, Liu traveled from Wuhan to Yichun for a meeting, and on the morning of his departure, he scheduled five surgeries, insisting that after the surgery, he drive her to Yichun himself.

Why don't you consider rescheduling the surgery? Liu Ruen said, Liu Zhiming told him, because the patients left Wuhan will not be reimbursed, want them to do surgery at home, willing to sacrifice their time.

In Liu's view, Liu Zhiming has sacrificed too much of his time to ensure that Wuhan residents have access to a high level of medical care locally. Liu Zhiming often told his friends, in Wuhan, Concord Hospital, Tongji Hospital, Zhongnan Hospital, People's Hospital neurosurgery is very powerful, Wuhan three hospitals to develop is not easy.

Pick-up, drop-off, morning shift, night shift, Liu Zhiming never seems to tire. "It's not easy for a doctor to get up early because he works three shifts, but every time I come down for dinner, he's waiting in the hall early, as he has for years, " Liu said.

The effort paid off, and the surgical research on trigeminal NEURALGIA and Hemifacial spasm was a huge success, and has since become one of the specialty businesses in Hubei Province. At the same time, the neurosurgery department in the Wuhan Sanyuan was classified as a separate department, with Liu Zhiming as its director.

After the establishment of the Department of neurosurgery, Liu Zhiming also actively pushed the department to participate in the assessment of key disciplines at the city level in Wuhan. During the assessment period, he was hands-on and actively prepared materials on the basis of enhancing business, and helped neurosurgery through the city-level evaluation of key disciplines.

Wu Wei, a doctor who also worked in the Wuhan Third Hospital, often went to the Department of neurosurgery to exchange work experience with Liu Zhiming and the doctors and nurses in the department. She often lamented that Liu Zhiming had "brought the department of neurosurgery too well. " "Some directors are very concerned about whether the operation is beautiful or not, and do not pay attention to management, but Liu Zhiming is very capable in medical treatment and management. ".

Anyone familiar with neurosurgery knows that patient recovery is especially important. In other departments are not equipped with a nutritionist, Liu Zhiming recruited a professional nutritionist to assist postoperative care.

Transferred to the medical director, Liu Zhiming also did not idle down, he proposed the establishment of the hospital's 120 emergency center, Wu Wei at this time became his subordinate. Wu Wei said, at the beginning of the establishment, Liu Zhiming with a few people planning, from "digging" to find a car, from the purchase of materials to set up a work system, everything is very concerned. In this way, the 120 emergency center realized from zero to have in Wuhan three hospitals, built three first aid stations.

In 2013, Liu Zhiming transferred to Wuchang Hospital Vice President, complete daily work, he also decided to set up a nutrition department, recruitment of professional business personnel, Wang Qian is the first nutritionist he recruited.

On the first day, Wang Qian reported in the human resources department and went to President Liu's office to discuss the work. Liu Zhiming has been busy, in the middle back to the office, said to her: "I bookcase a lot of books, you first look, I busy back. ".

Liu Zhiming had been busy for a long time. When he came back, his shoes were covered with mud. Wang Qian thought at the time, "the Dean is really hands-on and very dedicated in his work. " Wang Qian said that Liu Zhiming attached great importance to the creation of the nutrition division and had been urging him to seek him directly if he had any difficulties, and that he would do his best to solve them.

Busy with the size of the hospital, Liu Zhiming rare on the way home show tired. Shi Yan, a former staff member at Wuchang Hospital who lives close to Liu Zhiming, sometimes asks her for a ride home. Many times, Liu Zhiming on a car fell asleep, "do not dare to talk to him, he is very tired look. ".

Two faces of seriousness and gentleness

In addition to academic and Scientific Research, Liu Zhiming devotes more attention to patients, even those who have been discharged from the hospital after surgery, and he often calls back to track their recovery.

Li Wei recalled to thepaper.cn that in 2008, Liu Zhiming went to the intensive care unit to find out about a patient whose facial spasm had not improved after surgery and stayed with the patient for a whole week without interruption.

Liu ruen is no stranger to such examples.

Once, when Liu Zhiming changed the dressing for the patient after the operation, he found some hematomas in the wound. In Liu Ruen's view, the work of dressing change need not director personally battle, and a small postoperative incision bleeding is also a normal phenomenon, according to the CT report can make a judgment, whether to deal with.

The next morning at 3:00, Liu Ruen's phone suddenly rang, is Liu Zhiming call. Turns out, he was worried about the patient's bleeding, and he wanted to check the CT remotely with a good friend. Ms Liu's judgment is that no special treatment is needed.

Liu Zhiming hung up the phone and ran back to the ward for observation. Two hours later, he sent another short message saying that the patient was in a lot of pain and the Hematoma was a little bigger. Liu ruen still thinks it doesn't need to be dealt with. Two hours later, it was 7 o'clock in the morning, Liu Zhiming called Liu Ruen again, the tone of the speech relaxed a lot, "the patient's Hematoma no longer changes, has been stable. ".

Or teach a new resident how to scrub. Once, a just assigned to Liu Zhiming Department of graduate students did not brush according to standard, directly into the operating room, Liu Zhiming immediately followed in, said to the graduate students "No" , asked him to brush again. Such a rigorous style, throughout his 29 years of practice.

"If a patient truly believes in you, it is through the services of a doctor -- The meticulous work, your patience, and your extraordinary skill -- that he has achieved it, " says Liu.

Preciseness is not Liu Zhiming's only face at work. He never takes a leadership position when dealing with subordinates, especially the younger generation in the "care" unit.

Zhang Li, a retired employee of Wuchang Hospital who worked with him for four years, recalled to thepaper.cn that Liu Zhiming had "worked hard" at the hospital's 120 emergency center because of its poor performance.

The troops and horses are not moving. The provisions go first. To improve the working and living conditions of the centre's staff, he had the hospital staff and "temporary stretcher bearers" whose homes he had renovated "so that they could work with dignity" . The effort paid off, with the Wuchang Hospital's emergency centre rising from the city's bottom to the top of the list.

Zhang Li choked up as she recalled the details of her work. Liu Zhiming often forget to eat because of busy work, sometimes, a few colleagues to eat together, and so on other people have finished, only he has not finished busy.

But even then busy, in many things, he still insisted on doing it himself. Zhang Li recalled that whenever the Union organized visits for retired workers, he always told them, "make sure to arrange for me to visit the old comrades in person when I am free. ".

Konishi, a nurse at Wuchang Hospital who was hired only last year, couldn't stop crying over the news on her phone screen. Liu Zhiming signed for her when she went through the entry formalities. Her first impression was that the dean was very approachable. He asked Konishi where she was from and told her to keep up the good work.

Konishi was joined the same year as Wong Jing. In November 2018, Liu Zhiming personally came to the Qiqihar Medical University of Heilongjiang to recruit staff, and Wong Jing was one of the psychiatrists he had personally selected. Learned that several girls living away from home is not easy, several people in the Nanhu Hospital district and no staff quarters, Liu Zhiming in the hospital for them to obtain two rooms as a dormitory, as a special care, "let us have the feeling of home. ".

Wong Jing told The Paper news that the last time he saw Liu Zhiming was eating in the staff canteen. Asked if it was all right, Liu Zhiming also took her to introduce her to other leaders. "This is the beautiful woman I recruited from the Northeast! " He said, i also care about whether she can adapt to the weather in Wuhan.

In addition to the care of life, Liu Zhiming is more willing to practice the opportunity to leave some to his staff, he in the side to teach. Under his leadership, his colleagues' business skills have improved rapidly, he said. "He taught us everything he knew, and even after he transferred to Wuchang Hospital, his colleagues in the department were still very concerned. ".

Almost all people familiar with Liu Zhiming do not want to believe that all hands-on God outside experts, no leadership framework of President Liu gone forever.

According to a Red Star News report, before the Department of Critical Care Medicine of Wuchang Hospital was taken over by the supporting medical team on January 26, the medical staff had worked without rest for nearly 30 consecutive days. At the time of being taken over, Wuchang Hospital admitted 469 patients with fever, of those, 30 were critically ill.

During the epidemic prevention period, the Wuchang Hospital also issued several announcements, requesting material assistance from the community. Li Wei believes that when the patient transfer, Liu Zhiming to personally calm the patient's mood, may be in the process of infection.

After the outbreak, Liu Ruen, who was far away in Beijing, only had a phone call with Liu Zhiming. It was the second day of the Lunar New Year. Liu Zhiming confided in his friend on the phone in a hoarse voice that he was having difficulty with the heavy workload and the shortage of beds in the courtyard, "It's a lot of work. ".

Did Not say a few words, the end of the receiver noisy environmental noise over the voice of Liu Zhiming, Liu Ruen know, he must be turned busy to go, then hurriedly hung up the phone. He didn't tell Liu that he was already in the intensive care unit.

Liu ruen would never have thought that a "goodbye" on the phone would be goodbye. At 9:30 p.m. on Feb. 17, he saw his best friend's life was in danger and immediately called, but no one answered.

On the morning of February 18th, after 17 hours of artificial lung treatment, Liu Zhiming left for good, becoming the eighth official medical officer to die on the front lines of the epidemic. Earlier, on Feb. 13, the National Institutes of Health reported 1,716 cases of new coronary pneumonia.

Learned that the news, Tu Han Jun can no longer control their emotions, tears, he seems to see Liu Zhiming fresh face, as if not left. As Liu Zhiming's professional enlightenment teacher, Tu Hanjun has handed down skills, in a long-term relationship, the two also teacher and friend. After taking up the leadership position, Liu Zhiming also often discussed the problem of hospital management with master.

"As an excellent doctor and hospital manager, he continued to lead by example in the face of the sudden outbreak of the disease and became the first hospital director to be killed in the fight against the disease, " Tu wrote at the end of his eulogy, liu Zhiming's eldest daughter is studying clinical medicine at Hubei Medical College, and he hopes to turn her into a good doctor like her father in the near future.

Wang Lunchang, the honorary director and former party secretary of the Taihe Hospital in Shiyan City, 80, also lamented the death of his former subordinate and wrote a poem, farewell Liu Zhiming: "coronaviruses abuse the world, the war of extermination of the Chinese plague is still raging. It is heard that Zhi Ming was buried in sand, and old tears still spring up like water. The war plague is still in a state of stagnation, and one can not relax the strings of war. The God of pestilence can not block the way of a doctor's soul, so one should carry on with a heroic spirit! "

Zhang Li, Wu Wei, Konishi, Wong Jing, Wang Qian, Shi Yan, and Li Wei are aliases
